x4freetext: Two large area (20 cm x 10 cm) position
placed at the folding angle for symmetric fission.
Detectors were placed on movable arms on both sides
of the beam at distance of 63.5 cm and 51.5 cm
The neutrons were detected in coincidence with
fission events by four neutron detectors, which
consisted of 12.7 cm diam. x 12.7 cm thick organic
liquid scintillator cells (BC501) coupled to 12.7 cm
Two silicon surface barrier detectors were
used at +-11.degr. for beam flux normalization purpose.
The data collection was triggered when a
fission fragment was detected in any one of the MWPCs
and the time of flight (TOF) of fission fragments and
neutrons were recorded in event mode for off-line
was made by using pulse shape discrimination (PSD)
based on the zero-crossing technique and the TOF.
